# Avoid Incorrect Jump Direction

Based on user feedback, the character sometimes performs a jump in the opposite direction immediately after landing (e.g., LeftJump -> RightJump) because the path node for the return jump is co-located with the landing point.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change enforces strict direction flow for jumps. After a **LeftJump**, any immediate **RightJump** nodes will be skipped, and vice-versa. This assumes the user always wants to continue in the general direction of the path and not immediately reverse course.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Logic
#### [MODIFY] [PathPlanningTracker.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs)
- In [ForceAdvanceTarget](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#1204-1411) method:
- Enhance the post-jump direction check loop.
- If `lastAction` was `LeftJump`:
    - Skip if candidate node action is `RightJump`.
    - Skip if candidate node position is to the right (existing check).
- If `lastAction` was `RightJump`:
    - Skip if candidate node action is `LeftJump`.
    - Skip if candidate node position is to the left (existing check).

